        "id": 2053750,
        "name": "Dennis Atick",
        "username": "Dennis_Atick",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dennis_atick/{size}/429_2.png",
        "created_at": "2016-11-11T17:11:27.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>You need to drink more Maranges!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2046380&amp;iNote=5999257\"><strong>1991 Bernard Bachelet Maranges 1er Cru La Fussi\u00e8re</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Maranges 1er Cru (11/10/2016)</em><br>\nStill kicking! Nose shows some sous bois and aged Pinot fruit. It\u2019s not elegant or especially complex, it leans toward thin with tart cherry fruit. Youthful fruit I will say. But it is a sound 25 yr old burg that is enjoyable, especially with my roast chicken and taters. Fun buy from Envoyer.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"http://www.cellartracker.com/\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 8,
